I"Ì<p>A new feature is included in the 2.0 version that makes it possible for you to set your website unavailable for visitors to access.</p>

<p>This feature itâ€™s most commonly used while fixing or improving website.</p>

<p><strong>To activate Maintenance Mode:</strong></p>

<ol>
  <li>Go to <strong>Admin Panel</strong></li>
  <li>Select <strong>Settings</strong> -&gt; <strong>General</strong></li>
  <li>Set <strong>Maintenance Mode</strong> option to <strong>ON</strong></li>
  <li>Click <strong>Save</strong> button</li>
</ol>

<p>While activated, anyone who tries to access will see following page. <strong>Only administrator can access</strong> and see whole website by logging in.</p>

